Reference Number: 9751
Job Title: HR Data Analyst
Business Unit: Emera Corporate Human Resources (HR)
Location: Halifax, NS
Type of Employment: Regular, Full Time
Anticipated Start Date: As soon as possible

The opportunity:

We are currently looking for a HR Data Analyst to join our Corporate HR team on a permanent basis. Reporting to the Manager, HR Process & Analytics, the HR Data Analyst will be responsible for collaborating with HR and Business team members across Emera’s international affiliated businesses to develop reporting and provide analytics expertise in support of our talent and business strategy. The HR Data Analyst serves as a cross-functional subject matter expert to the Corporate HR group, continuously assessing our data for insights, innovation of processes, and industry trends. In this exciting new role, you will be encouraged to innovate, modernize, and act as a thoughtful leader.

Accountabilities:
More specifically, in this role you will:

Support and assist in developing a data strategy for the business;

Serve as a subject matter expert in HR Data and Analytics, Technology, and related processes;

Manage the delivery of analytics and insights by compiling and analyzing large sets of workforce data (e.g. headcount, recruitment, development, turnover, hires, promotions, diversity, exit interviews, workforce demographic, engagement);

Understand our business processes and translate them into measurable data or reporting requirements including content, frequency, and data source;

Review reporting processes and its results to ensure value and customer satisfaction;
Continuously seek opportunities to innovate and improve while creating efficiencies;

Provide input into the design of new systems and applications, participate in testing and support deployment to our end users.

Skills, Competencies and Experience:

As the ideal candidate you recognize yourself in most of the following competencies, and possess or are working towards the desired skills and experience listed below:

A Bachelor’s Degree in a Data Science-related field: preferably with a quantitative focus, such as Engineering, Statistics, Applied Mathematics, Economics, or Computer Science or equivalent experience;

Proven analytical skills through education or 5+ years’ experience in a data analytics/information management field;

Previous experience working in a Human Resources environment and HRIS systems (e.g. Peoplesoft) would be beneficial;

Strong proficiency in MS Excel including experience with advanced formulas, Excel VBA/macros, Python, SQL;
Previous experience with BI and data visualization tools such as Tableau, including Tableau Prep Builder and Tableau Server, considered an asset;
A self-motivated individual who brings strong quantitative skills and high attention to detail;

Strong communication skills and demonstrated ability to present to a diverse group in a compelling and influential manner;

Superior decision making and problem-solving skills with the ability to develop, recommend and implement innovative solutions;

A strong collaborator and team player who excels at facilitating outcomes with the needs of various stakeholders in mind while effectively prioritizing and managing multiple priorities in a fast-paced dynamic environment while meeting deadlines;

Proven ability to manage sensitive and confidential data;

Other combinations of related education and experience may be considered.

We will assess the above qualifications using one of more of the following tools: written examination, standardized tests, oral presentations, interview(s), and reference checks.

Why join Emera?

Emera is one of Atlantic Canada’s largest publicly traded companies, and a North American Top 20 utility. Our ability to serve more customers in more places is thanks to the commitment of our 7,100 employees in Canada, the USA, and the Caribbean. As we develop, we are excited to welcome new team members who are committed to our purpose and our approach to business. Emera values people who believe that safety and health, relationships, and excellence are integral to how we work. In return, we value the diversity of our people and invest in their growth through:

competitive compensation packages: including a comprehensive pension and benefits plan and employee-sponsored saving plans;

opportunities for career growth: including a strategic focus on employee development plans, opportunities to advance within and between our affiliate companies, sponsored education programs;

giving back to communities: including corporate investments in the places where our people live and work; employee dollars-for-doers and fundraising-matching programs, scholarships for children of employees.

At Emera our employees are our greatest strength. Our Leadership Competencies set standards that advance our business strategy, deliver results for customers, and provide career development for employees. As the ideal candidate, you are a strong leader who works to advance a safety culture by placing safety, health, and wellness above any business objective. You understand the importance of strong inclusive teams and develop employees to take on challenges and opportunities. As the HR Data Analyst, you encourage innovation, lead change to ensure continuous improvement demonstrating integrity, and set clear expectations for a high standard of work performance for yourself and the Corporate HR team. Lastly as the successful candidate it is your responsibility to connect every decision to the company strategy and apply sound judgment to translate new ideas into actions.

Reports to: Manager, HR Process & Analytics

Application Requirement: To apply, please click on the blue ‘APPLY NOW’ button in this job posting, complete all required information fields, and attach your cover letter and resume into one single file to the online form.

Salary: Commensurate with qualifications and experience.

Application Deadline: We encourage you to apply at your earliest opportunity but no later than Wednesday April 20, 2022. Late applications may not receive consideration.

Recruitment and Promotion Policy: When filling vacant positions, we are determined to hire the best candidates available. We are committed to providing employees with a fair and equal opportunity to compete for jobs. Hiring and promotion of employees is based on skills, capabilities, knowledge and demonstrated abilities.

In accordance with Emera’s occupational health and safety program and the Emera Vaccine Program, subject to any approved accommodation, all employees are required to be fully vaccinated against COVID-19. For clarity, “fully vaccinated” means having the number of doses or combination of doses of a vaccine approved by Health Canada or local public health agencies in the jurisdiction in which they will be employed.

At Emera we value diversity, equity, and inclusion. We strongly encourage applications from all qualified candidates, including persons who identify as racially visible, Indigenous, persons with disabilities, women in underrepresented roles and members of the LGBTQ+ community. Applicants from these equity groups may self-identify through the on-line application process. Emera supports candidates and employees with access and accommodation needs.

Company Description
VOSKER is inspired by the desire of surpassing oneself and challenging limits. We are one of the world's leaders in Remote Area Monitoring, with satisfied customers in more than 50 countries. We are also one of the Top 100 Fastest Growing Canadian Companies in 2021 (Source: Globe and Mail).
We are motivated by performance, innovation, and family.
Our willingness to push ourselves and our limits allows us to revolutionize the field of safety, technology, and outdoor activity through our innovative, A.I. driven products and services.
To continue our growth, we are looking for a Senior Data Analyst, Business Performance for our VOSKER division.
As part of this role, reporting directly to the Vice-President, Marketing and Sales, you will work with the Management team to optimize the performance of every acquisition, upselling and retention channels. If you are passionate about Insights and Business Performance, this role is for you!

Job Description
Your mission :
Strategic : In collaboration with the Vice-President, Marketing and Sales and the Management team, to support the strategy development and the implementation of a data driven, Business Performance DNA;
Analytics : Through data organization and analysis, to identify Insights, in order to optimize the Business Performance of our projects, campaigns, price elasticity, sales conversion funnels, customers lifetime value, offers, partnerships, etc.;
Reporting : To create, use and present dashboards and analytics reports, per project, per period, per objective and to measure results against comparables;
Predictive : To develop and implement predictive algorithms and structure the data in order to support marketing individualization (CRM);
Market Insight : Lead market studies, surveys, competitor positioning analysis, market potential research and customers segments analysis.

Qualifications

5 to 10 years of relevant experience in data management, analysis, visualization, interpretation and insight, in a Business Performance context;
A bachelor's degree in Statistics, Mathematics, Data processing or any other relevant field;
Interest in the Innovation and Technology sector;
Outstanding abilities to transform data into Insights and Business recommendations;
Remarkable vulgarization skills;
Strong experience with analytics tools (SQL, SAS, G.A, etc.) and visualization tools (Power B.I, Klipfolio, etc.);
Strong experience with database, JavaScript and Salesforce;
Concrete realizations in Predictive models/algorithms implementation;
Bilingualism (French and English) spoken and written, essential.

Additional Information
Why choose VOSKER?
First of all, a work environment where performance, innovation, and family are valued!
A work-life balance.
Schedule flexibility for early and late risers.
No traffic jam, you can work directly from home.
A 24/7 free access to online doctors.
A diversified company with a variety of challenges: you can’t get bored.
A group insurance, because we want to take care of our people.
Equal access to employment:
At VOSKER, we value the essence of each person and celebrate the diversity that allows us to redefine what is possible. We are committed to collaboration by providing a healthy and inclusive work environment where all voices are heard.
Please do not hesitate to contact us if you have specific needs to make this recruitment process more accessible to you.
It is now your turn to tell us about yourself. All you have to do is apply!

ALS fournit une large gamme de services de tests et d’analyses à une variété de marchés et d’industries à travers le monde. Nous sommes un chef de file dans l’industrie des services d’analyses et avons établi une réputation enviable en regard de la qualité de nos résultats et de services à la clientèle.

Laboratory Analyst

Location: ALS Metallurgy, Kamloops

Reports to: Manager, Analytical Lab

Position Type: Permanent, full-time

About the Position
This position is responsible for using standard procedures for fire assay and wet assay to produce high quality analytical results.

Specific Responsibilities

Conduct laboratory preparatory work including weighing and solution preparation;
Use established procedures for chemical/instrumental analysis;
Ensure analytical quality of analysis and timely reporting of analysis to meet required deadlines;
Use Microsoft Excel to create reports and evaluate data;
Perform day-to-day routine care of equipment;
Assist others, as required, to meet workload and turnaround commitments in the laboratory;
Maintain a clean work environment;
Observe established safety regulations and comply with all ALS health and safety policies and procedures;
Other duties as assigned.

Required Knowledge, Skills & Abilities

Fire assay and/or analytical laboratory experience preferred;
Skill in utilizing laboratory equipment and computers to conduct sample and data analysis, interpreting analytical data and evaluating results;
Detail oriented with a strong commitment to quality and able to evaluate and verify results obtained in the analytical process;
Strong organizational skills, highly motivated and able to work with strict deadlines;
Skilled in effective English communication, both orally and in writing;
Ability to establish and maintain effective working conditions with co-workers and work constructively as part of a team;
Ability to work safely and follow safety regulations, policies and procedures.

Required Qualifications

Recognized degree or Diploma in Science;

Physical Demands

Manual dexterity and ability to lift 25 kg pounds;
Wear issued personal protective equipment (PPE) such as dust masks, gloves etc., when required;

Additional Information

Competitive wages
